TITLE UUDeferredValue for Expensive Derived Renders
UUDEFERREDVALUE FOR EXPENSIVE DERIVED RENDERS
When user input triggers expensive computations or renders, UUDeferredValue to keep the input responsive. The deferred value lags behind, allowing React to prioritize the input update and render the expensive result when idle. 
Incorrect (input feels laggy while filtering): 
CODE tsx 299CHARS
Correct (input stays snappy, results render when ready): 
CODE tsx 514CHARS
WTU: 
Filtering/searching large lists Expensive visualizations (charts, graphs) reacting to input Any derived state that causes noticeable render delays 
Note: Wrap the expensive computation in useMemo with the deferred value as a dependency, otherwise it still runs on every render. 
REFERENCE [React useDeferredValue](https://react.dev/reference/react/useDeferredValue)